claim.claim-text:
A landing gear system for an aircraft, the landing gear system comprising:
a shock strut assembly having a centerline axis, the shock strut assembly being coupled to the airframe with a universal joint;
a drag brace assembly coupled to an airframe of the aircraft with a spindle, the spindle being rotatable about a spindle axis; and
a radius rod rotatably coupled to the airframe of the aircraft;
wherein the radius rod and the shock strut assembly are retractable about a retraction rotation axis;
wherein the spindle axis has a common intersection point with the centerline axis and the retraction rotation axis.

The landing gear system according to claim 1, further comprising:
a tire member mounted to an axle on the shock strut assembly;
wherein the orientation of the spindle axis causes a translation of the tire member to have a longitudinal component during a compression of the shock strut assembly.

The landing gear system according to claim 8, further comprising:
a radius rod rotatably coupled to the airframe of the aircraft;
wherein the radius rod and the shock strut assembly are retractable about a retraction rotation axis.

The landing gear system according to claim 8 or any preceding claim, further comprising:
a collar for coupling the drag brace assembly to the shock strut assembly;
wherein the spindle is located aft and inboard to the collar.

The landing gear system according to claim 8 or any preceding claim, further comprising:
an upper torque arm;
a lower torque arm;
a radius rod, or the radius rod, coupled between the airframe and the upper torque arm;
wherein a compression of a shock absorber portion of the shock strut assembly imparts a levering force that causes rotation in part around the spindle axis.

The landing gear system according to claim 8 or any preceding claim, further comprising:
an actuator, or the actuator, coupled to the drag brace assembly;
wherein selective actuation of the actuator can retract and deploy the landing gear system by rotation about a retraction rotation axis.

An aircraft comprising:
a fuselage having an airframe;
a rotor system;
a retractable main landing gear system, comprising:
a shock strut assembly having a centerline axis, the shock strut assembly being coupled to the airframe, the shock strut assembly having a shock absorber;
a drag brace assembly rotatably coupled to the airframe so as define a spindle axis; and
a tire member;
wherein a compression of the shock absorber causes the tire member to translate in a stroke path, the stroke path having an aft directional component.

The aircraft according to claim 14 or claim 15, the retractable main landing gear system further comprising:
a radius rod rotatably coupled to the airframe of the aircraft;
a universal joint coupling the shock strut assembly to the airframe;
wherein the retractable main landing gear system is retractable about a retraction rotation axis.

1. An aircraft (101) having an airframe (213, 245, 251) and a landing gear system (113) comprising:
a shock strut assembly (203) having a centerline axis, the shock strut assembly being coupled to the airframe with a universal joint;
a drag brace assembly (205) coupled to the airframe (245) of the aircraft with a spindle (243), the spindle being rotatable about a spindle axis (247); and
a radius rod (207) rotatably coupled to the airframe (251) of the aircraft;
wherein the radius rod (207) and the shock strut assembly (203) are retractable about a retraction rotation axis (221);
wherein the spindle axis (231) has a common intersection point with the centerline axis (225) and the retraction rotation axis (221);
the landing gear further comprising a tire member (209) mounted to an axle on the shock strut assembly (203);
wherein the orientation of the spindle axis causes a translation of the tire member (209) to have a longitudinal component during a compression of the shock strut assembly (203).

7. The aircraft according to claim 1, further comprising:
a collar (223), or the collar (223) for coupling the drag brace assembly to the shock strut assembly (203);
wherein the spindle is located aft and inboard to the collar (223).

8. The aircraft according to claim 7 or any preceding claim, further comprising:
an upper torque arm (225) and;
a lower torque arm;

wherein the radius rod (207) is coupled between the airframe (251) and the upper torque arm (255); and
wherein a compression of a shock absorber portion (227) of the shock strut assembly (203) causes lower torque arm (257) to move toward radius rod (207) causing the upper torque arm (255) to act against radius rod (207) thereby causing rotation of the strut assembly (203) about the spindle axis (247) of axle spindle (231).

9. The aircraft according to any preceding claim, further comprising:
an actuator (201), or the actuator (201), coupled to the drag brace assembly (205);
wherein selective actuation of the actuator (201) can retract and deploy the landing gear system by rotation about the retraction rotation axis (221).
